Vice President Mike Pence has appointed Lieutenant General (Ret) Joseph Keith Kellogg, Jr. as the National Security Advisor to the Vice President. General Kellogg will also continue to serve as an Assistant to President Donald J. Trump. General Kellogg has a distinguished military career, having served in the United States Army from 1967 to 2003, including two tours during the Vietnam War. He has received several awards and honors for his service. Previously, General Kellogg served as Acting National Security Advisor to President Trump and as Chief of Staff and Executive Secretary of the National Security Council. Vice President Pence expressed his gratitude for General Kellogg's willingness to serve and highlighted his experience in national security and foreign policy matters.